The Busia government will start distributing milk to public Early Childhood Development Education centres for free, a senior county official has said.Bunyala subcounty administrator Francis Omillo said, &ldquo;Milk helps develop the minds and reasoning capacity of children. This will enable them to be active in class and improve their academic performance.&rdquo; He spoke during the Mashujaa Day celebrations at Budalang&rsquo;i Primary School last Thursday. Two hundred ECDE classrooms &ndash; at least six in each of the 35 wards &ndash; have been built in three years, Omillo said. He said bursaries have been distributed to secondary school students, adding that the process for the 2016-17 financial year has started.Omillo urged needy students to pick bursary forms. &ldquo;A revolving fund for university and college students will be ready once proposed regulations are passed by the county assembly,&rdquo; he said.